WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:12.190 --> 00:00:13.490
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: Good morning.

00:00:13.490 --> 00:00:15.440
I'm Carla Hayden, the
Librarian of Congress,

00:00:15.440 --> 00:00:16.810
and I want to welcome you

00:00:16.810 --> 00:00:19.960
to this very special
story time at the library.

00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:21.960
I love reading; don't you?

00:00:21.960 --> 00:00:25.850
It's so much fun to let
our imaginations run wild.

00:00:25.850 --> 00:00:27.750
We're excited to be teaming

00:00:27.750 --> 00:00:30.920
up with Miss Dolly
Parton's Imagination Library

00:00:30.920 --> 00:00:33.910
to introduce you to
some wonderful authors

00:00:33.910 --> 00:00:35.900
who will share their
stories with us.

00:00:35.900 --> 00:00:39.830
Miss Parton's work through
her Imagination Library

00:00:39.830 --> 00:00:41.920
is awe-inspiring.

00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:46.060
She and her team have given
away over 100 million books

00:00:46.060 --> 00:00:50.910
to help encourage young readers
like you across the world.

00:00:50.910 --> 00:00:53.790
Here at the Library of
Congress, we share that passion

00:00:53.790 --> 00:00:57.510
for developing young readers
and we know that the best way

00:00:57.510 --> 00:01:02.770
to encourage people like you
to read is to make reading fun,

00:01:02.770 --> 00:01:04.760
so that's what we're here to do.

00:01:04.760 --> 00:01:06.790
I hope you enjoy
today's story time.

00:01:06.790 --> 00:01:12.200
Even more, I hope you keep
reading at home and having fun.

00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:17.620
Today we will warm up by singing
some songs, touching your toes,

00:01:17.620 --> 00:01:22.390
and then get comfortable and
get ready to hear stories.

00:01:22.390 --> 00:01:25.410
Now let's get started.

